8QTPzBJfy-mDvh2RP3pTLNNK3_g73XsC3MBNWNjPjq1sTqqItpAX_xboHB2WnGI_lkxAIhp3stKrjWZBfJ0oucsjzmx5u-g6b8pPIMiYiuAm1veBscDZhqpCW0sagdSDTGZFs20lnLXbaa-XrCekKKn7_6x_czFpHXV5fe1gIXq318fyleT4rDCI-NaAZJCPsq7TI4lqoRjNIadFCVrHZ81KgKAUKPhlfblkCCYDWBMo-YDT7HPQpooWefXRsMErghZcQDTB9MEfUGwYBw3xaivxRjPxmBek_3HCsF5BZVsMOC-y_U7pDnqeTFUM0t4ZFKlq14CNThyW-h-QQ4N8oWrDQWJB4Ozp1DMi5EKkuB15Xw2NunpW5DwxSoOvnFGvxTPMyV6RlZZCpXVcC4Hy1rdnD9zkm2GUiiFdGJA2mF3FU7zF8LgCMBbjHYOSXfojMuW5q25RmQn1fm5p4vg-XUFgHSEoS8kKcYNNW0GcieKX2wWJtca0K6wwOGw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing library setup needs**\\n\\nI'm considering whether the library requires additional setup beyond the standard test scaffold. I think the usual scaffold typically includes just the library dependencies. But, maybe additional configurations, plugins, or tools could enhance testing coverage. I need to evaluate what’s provided by default versus any specific needs that might come up in real usage scenarios. So, let me dive deeper into the functions and documentation to ensure everything is covered for meaningful testing!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"jackrabbit-webdav is an in-process WebDAV server/client utility library, but its servlet-facing APIs are central to meaningful coverage and the artifact declares javax.servlet:servlet-api as provided, so the generated test scaffold needs that test dependency explicitly.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Core library classes such as WebdavRequestImpl, WebdavResponseImpl, AbstractWebdavServlet, InputContextImpl, OutputContextImpl, and header parsers use javax.servlet types, while the Maven artifact marks servlet-api as provided and it is not reliably available from a normal test scaffold.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker service or external WebDAV server is required; focus on in-process coverage of XML/DAV method construction, headers, reports, properties, and servlet-facing adapters using lightweight mocks or stubs. Use javax.servlet-era APIs, not jakarta.servlet.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The library is old and uses pre-Jakarta javax.servlet APIs; using jakarta.servlet would not compile.\",\n    \"A missing SLF4J binding may produce warnings but is not required for meaningful coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_00855e3aa7250c2e016a41f6d13c8c819394c9e6d5f230bd51\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 806, "output": 1322, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37968, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782707906838, "responseId": "resp_00855e3aa7250c2e016a41f6c375148193a6b3c4d043e4d788"}}
